---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Mercedes-AMG Formula 1 Car">

    <main class="main">

    <!-- Page Title -->
    <div class="page-title">
      <div class="breadcrumbs">
        <nav aria-label="breadcrumb">
          <ol class="breadcrumb">
            <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/"><i class="bi bi-house"></i> Home</a></li>
            <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/portfolio">Portfolio</a></li>
            <li class="breadcrumb-item active current">Mercedes-AMG Formula 1 Car</li>
          </ol>
        </nav>
      </div>

      <div class="container section-title pb-0">
        <h2>Mercedes-AMG Formula 1 Car</h2>
        <div class="title-shape">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 200 20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <path d="M 0,10 C 40,0 60,20 100,10 C 140,0 160,20 200,10" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div><!-- End Section Title -->
    </div><!-- End Page Title -->

    <!-- Portfolio Details Section -->
    <section id="portfolio-details" class="portfolio-details section">

      <div class="container">

        <div class="row gy-4 g-lg-5">
          <div class="col-lg-6">
            <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/36.webp" class="img-fluid mb-4 rounded-4" alt="" loading="lazy">
            <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/37.webp" class="img-fluid mb-4 rounded-4" alt="" loading="lazy">
            <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/38.webp" class="img-fluid mb-4 rounded-4" alt="" loading="lazy">
            <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/39.webp" class="img-fluid mb-4 rounded-4" alt="" loading="lazy">
            <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/40.webp" class="img-fluid mb-4 rounded-4" alt="" loading="lazy">
          </div>

          <div class="col-lg-6">

            <div class="position-sticky" style="top: 40px">
              <div class="portfolio-description">
                <h2>Overview</h2>
                <p>
                  High-detail CAD reconstruction of a modern Formula 1 car developed through image-based reference and reverse engineering, focusing on dimensional accuracy and advanced surface modeling.
                </p>

                <div class="portfolio-info mt-5">
                  <h2>Specifications</h2>
                  <ul>
                    <li><strong>Model Type:</strong> Full vehicle assembly</li>
                    <li><strong>Source:</strong> Image reference + reverse engineering</li>
                    <li><strong>Focus:</strong> High-detail surface modeling</li>
                    <li><strong>Accuracy:</strong> Dimensionally consistent proportions</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <h2>Design Constraints</h2>
                <p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Reconstruct complex aerodynamic geometry from limited reference data</li>
                    <li>Maintain proportional accuracy across full vehicle assembly</li>
                    <li>Ensure smooth surface continuity across interconnected components</li>
                    <li>Handle high geometric complexity without surface breakdown</li>
                  </ul>
                </p>

                <h2>Design Approach</h2>
                <p>
                  The model was developed using a combination of reference-based reconstruction and reverse engineering techniques to capture the overall geometry and aerodynamic form of a modern Formula 1 car.
                  <br><br>
                  Advanced surface modeling tools were extensively used to achieve smooth transitions, complex curvature, and high-detail component integration across the full assembly.
                </p>

                <h2>Key Features</h2>
                <p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Full vehicle assembly with integrated components</li>
                    <li>Extremely detailed surface modeling across aerodynamic elements</li>
                    <li>High geometric complexity with clean surface continuity</li>
                    <li>Accurate representation of modern Formula 1 design language</li>
                  </ul>
                </p>

                <h2>Outcome</h2>
                <p>
                  Delivered a dimensionally accurate and visually refined Formula 1 car assembly, demonstrating advanced CAD capability in handling complex surface geometry and large-scale assemblies.
                </p>

              </div>

              <div class="portfolio-info mt-5">
                <h3>Project information</h3>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Category</strong> Independent Project</li>
                  <li><strong>Project date</strong> November, 2025</li>
                  <li><strong>Project URL</strong> <a href="https://grabcad.com/library/mercedes-amg-formula-1-car-1">https://grabcad.com/library/mercedes-amg-formula-1-car-1</a></li>
                  <li><strong>Workflow Recording</strong> <a href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLp7dj9uy6_77gfimuYpTyRSo0rYJQ_4Yj">YouTube Playlist</a></li>
                  <li><a href="https://grabcad.com/library/mercedes-amg-formula-1-car-1" class="btn-visit align-self-start">Download CAD Files</a></li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

    </section><!-- /Portfolio Details Section -->

    </main>

</BaseLayout>